Preheat oven to 400 degrees. 

> If you know you're making this recipe in advance, take the pizza dough out of the fridge to come to room temperature.

Par-bake the dough: using your hands, stretch out the @Pizza Dough{10%ounce} into a rough 1⁄4-inch thick rectangle. Place onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and prick all over with a #fork{}. Place in the oven for about ~{15%minutes}, until beginning to brown on the edges.

> If you have a rolling pin or wine bottle, you can use it to roll out the dough on a lightly floured surface.

Meanwhile, tear the @Basil{1%unit}(torn) leaves. Halve the @Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Thinly slice the @Fresh Mozzarella{8%ounce}.

Assemble the flatbread: Spread the par-baked flatbread with @Pesto{3%tablespoon} and top with the sliced mozzarella, heirloom tomatoes. Return to the oven until cheese begins to bubble, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Toss the @Arugula{4%ounce} with @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the flatbread along with the basil. Cut the flatbread into squares and enjoy!